1
00:00:00,880 --> 00:00:02,340
Hello and welcome.

2
00:00:02,340 --> 00:00:08,000
Today we'll look at volume, based on Wyckoff
theory, as well as discuss how to read volume

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,630
in combination with price, and additionally
we'll showcase several strategies you could

4
00:00:13,630 --> 00:00:17,960
apply for day trading, swing trading and even
scalping.

5
00:00:17,960 --> 00:00:24,730
So if you could… like, subscribe to the
channel and stick around for the full video.

6
00:00:24,730 --> 00:00:27,589
Volume is the ultimate leading indicator.

7
00:00:27,589 --> 00:00:32,520
When there is unusually high volume in any
given time period (which could be 5 minutes,

8
00:00:32,520 --> 00:00:37,610
an hour, a day, or a week), then the price
tends to continue in the same direction in

9
00:00:37,610 --> 00:00:39,020
the future.

10
00:00:39,020 --> 00:00:42,480
This principle applies to all financial markets.

11
00:00:42,480 --> 00:00:48,050
When prices are rising, the market will not
decrease purely as a result of low volume

12
00:00:48,050 --> 00:00:51,830
but will simply move sideways as it takes
a breather.

13
00:00:51,830 --> 00:00:57,130
Conversely any reversal from a falling market
cannot occur without an increase in volume,

14
00:00:57,130 --> 00:01:02,530
and is sometimes also referred to as a volume
climax.

15
00:01:02,530 --> 00:01:07,350
Volume confirms the strength of a trend or
suggests its weakness.

16
00:01:07,350 --> 00:01:12,369
Because if the market is rising, and volume
increasing, then this suggests that we have

17
00:01:12,369 --> 00:01:16,159
a strong trend supported by an increasing
number of buyers.

18
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:22,060
Think about it, if this was selling volume
coming into the market, then prices would

19
00:01:22,060 --> 00:01:26,340
fall, or perhaps move into sideways congestion
before falling.

20
00:01:26,340 --> 00:01:31,359
As this is not the case, we can therefore
conclude that the volume is BUYING volume,

21
00:01:31,359 --> 00:01:34,600
and you expect the trend to continue.

22
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:40,119
Conversely, if you have a rising trend but
falling volume, then this is WEAK.

23
00:01:40,119 --> 00:01:45,420
It’s logic, if the buyers are still in the
market, then this would be represented by

24
00:01:45,420 --> 00:01:51,579
RISING volume, and in this example we have
FALLING volume, so we can assume here that

25
00:01:51,579 --> 00:01:54,130
the buyers are NO LONGER INTERESTED.

26
00:01:54,130 --> 00:01:57,890
The trend is running out of steam and becoming
exhausted.

27
00:01:57,890 --> 00:02:00,859
This is the first sign of a POSSIBLE change
in trend.

28
00:02:00,859 --> 00:02:06,119
The buyers have left the market, and MAY now
be replaced with SELLERS.

29
00:02:06,119 --> 00:02:11,450
In a trend, the volume will go with the trend,
so expect to see the volume fall away in the

30
00:02:11,450 --> 00:02:13,160
pullback of the trend.

31
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:15,370
This is NORMAL volume behavior.

32
00:02:15,370 --> 00:02:20,530
The buyers are taking a rest, before re-entering
the market to buy once more.

33
00:02:20,530 --> 00:02:26,230
WHY? - because there has been NO SELLING CLIMAX
to signal a change in trend.

34
00:02:26,230 --> 00:02:31,840
If we see the following in an uptrend, with
an ultra-high volume bar appearing, then this

35
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:39,660
is a signal that the trend is about to reverse,
as volume climaxes OFTEN highlight price reversals.

36
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:45,270
This is particularly true if the extreme volume
is associated with no equivalent reaction

37
00:02:45,270 --> 00:02:46,720
in the price.

38
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:52,540
According to Wyckoff’s third law, if the
market requires effort (VOLUME) to rise and

39
00:02:52,540 --> 00:02:58,430
fall, the if the market has failed to rise
with significant volume, then clearly the

40
00:02:58,430 --> 00:03:03,800
market is resistant to any further increase,
and this volume must therefore be considered

41
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,920
to be SELLING volume.

42
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:11,290
If it were BUYING volume then the market would
have risen strongly.

43
00:03:11,290 --> 00:03:16,870
Here we can see that the market has been rising
strongly, with increasing volume, a positive

44
00:03:16,870 --> 00:03:17,870
sign.

45
00:03:17,870 --> 00:03:23,260
However, on the last bar, the volume has been
ultra-high, but the market has fallen with

46
00:03:23,260 --> 00:03:25,410
a narrow spread price bar.

47
00:03:25,410 --> 00:03:27,010
What’s happening here?

48
00:03:27,010 --> 00:03:34,280
In simple terms the buyers are no longer interested
at this price and a trend reversal is imminent.

49
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:39,560
If the volume bar was BUYING volume then the
market would have continued to rise as in

50
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:41,370
the previous bar.

51
00:03:41,370 --> 00:03:47,350
Instead it has failed to rise and the price
spread of the bar is narrow, so this MUST

52
00:03:47,350 --> 00:03:51,440
be selling volume coming into the market.

53
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:57,220
Points where the market trades on high volume
are the points of strong support and resistance,

54
00:03:57,220 --> 00:04:01,080
and are the first signs of a change in trend
or a breakout.

55
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:06,790
Volume helps us to confirm the potential breakout
from an area of price congestion.

56
00:04:06,790 --> 00:04:12,690
In this example, we can see that we have high
volume at the bottom of each market reversal,

57
00:04:12,690 --> 00:04:17,190
which is suggesting BUYING or ACCUMULATION
at these points.

58
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:22,850
The support area confirms this view, so that
when we FINALLY see the breakout we have a

59
00:04:22,850 --> 00:04:28,440
GREAT signal from our volume bars, that this
is a GENUINE breakout and therefore a LOW

60
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:30,760
RISK TRADE.

61
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:36,940
In this example, the high volume is at the
TOP of each trend, so in this case we can

62
00:04:36,940 --> 00:04:42,870
assume that this is SELLING volume with the
market creating a region of price resistance

63
00:04:42,870 --> 00:04:44,620
in this case.

64
00:04:44,620 --> 00:04:50,770
As this is selling volume, then when we see
the breakout to the down side, VOLUME once

65
00:04:50,770 --> 00:04:57,360
again VALIDATES this breakout, as we have
seen the HIGH volume bars on each FAILED attempt

66
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,060
to move higher.

67
00:04:59,060 --> 00:05:04,320
Once again we have a low risk entry, confirmed
by our volume.

68
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:09,950
Breakouts and market spikes can be validated
or voided with the help of volume.

69
00:05:09,950 --> 00:05:15,040
Without volume, we are merely guessing at
the future direction of the market.

70
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:21,910
With volume, we have an insight into the market,
and whether the interest is buying or selling.

71
00:05:21,910 --> 00:05:28,410
However, just like price, volume in isolation
tells us very little about the market’s

72
00:05:28,410 --> 00:05:29,830
future direction.

73
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:33,970
All it can signal on its own is interest in
a market or event.

74
00:05:33,970 --> 00:05:40,090
For this we need to combine price and volume
together to give us the most powerful analytical

75
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:44,710
tool available, which will reveal the market’s
future direction.

76
00:05:44,710 --> 00:05:49,650
As Wyckoff said: “all you need to know can
be found in price and volume.”

77
00:05:49,650 --> 00:05:54,639
From Wyckoff I learnt that price alone can
only tell you what is a market’s present

78
00:05:54,639 --> 00:05:58,600
technical position and where the trend is
probably headed.

79
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:04,030
That volume determines the trend with more
accuracy and detects turning points.

80
00:06:04,030 --> 00:06:08,310
But together, they form a complete picture.

81
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:09,310
Volume expresses interest and enthusiasm.

82
00:06:09,310 --> 00:06:13,410
Volume is the fuel of the market, it is what
drives the market, and without it, the market

83
00:06:13,410 --> 00:06:15,420
will simply drift.

84
00:06:15,420 --> 00:06:18,040
Volume exposes the truth of the market.

85
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:20,110
Volume reveals conviction in the market.

86
00:06:20,110 --> 00:06:25,740
If the market is moving higher, but with falling
or low volume, then this is simply telling

87
00:06:25,740 --> 00:06:28,460
us that this is not a genuine move.

88
00:06:28,460 --> 00:06:34,630
Equally, if the market is falling with falling
volume, then once again this is not a genuine

89
00:06:34,630 --> 00:06:35,630
move.

90
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:39,240
I know I’m repeating myself, but this is
so simple and powerful.

91
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:45,910
On their own, price and volume only reveal
a part of market information.

92
00:06:45,910 --> 00:06:48,790
After all, price tells you a number.

93
00:06:48,790 --> 00:06:53,240
Volume on its own only tells us there is interest,
and nothing else.

94
00:06:53,240 --> 00:07:00,080
However, when combined, the true market intent
is revealed giving clear signals of both buying

95
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:05,180
and selling interest, something that would
not be revealed by either on their own.

96
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:11,979
In simple terms, the more people that participate
in a price move, or in our case the more volume

97
00:07:11,979 --> 00:07:17,290
associated with a price move, the more that
price move is validated.

98
00:07:17,290 --> 00:07:22,470
When there is low volume, few buyers, then
our price is simply not validated.

99
00:07:22,470 --> 00:07:24,650
It really is that simple.

100
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:28,590
Let’s talk about volume and news announcements.

101
00:07:28,590 --> 00:07:34,160
The markets, as we know, are always full with
news of every type, from the daily release

102
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:40,310
of fundamental and economic data, to the political
statements from governments, to the latest

103
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:42,790
announcement from a central bank.

104
00:07:42,790 --> 00:07:48,570
All of these pieces of news are absorbed by
the markets and built into the latest price

105
00:07:48,570 --> 00:07:49,570
action.

106
00:07:49,570 --> 00:07:56,080
Now, as this new information is released into
the public domain, volume reveals the effect

107
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:58,040
of this information on price.

108
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:03,290
By watching the change in volume, as this
information is released, we can instantly

109
00:08:03,290 --> 00:08:09,360
see how the markets are reacting to the news,
and how quickly the latest piece of news is

110
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:13,650
being absorbed by the various market participants.

111
00:08:13,650 --> 00:08:18,889
What this means in simple terms is that the
volume substantiates the importance of the

112
00:08:18,889 --> 00:08:19,889
release.

113
00:08:19,889 --> 00:08:25,759
If the volume rises on the news and the price
rises in tandem, then the market is placing

114
00:08:25,759 --> 00:08:29,770
significant emphasis on this piece of news.

115
00:08:29,770 --> 00:08:34,010
Clearly in this case the price is being validated
by the volume surge.

116
00:08:34,010 --> 00:08:40,370
Conversely, if the volume fails to rise on
the news, then the market and the market participants

117
00:08:40,370 --> 00:08:46,580
have clearly discounted this item, and consider
it to be unimportant or irrelevant, as they

118
00:08:46,580 --> 00:08:49,370
now wait for the next release to arrive.

119
00:08:49,370 --> 00:08:55,420
Let’s look at a few more examples of how
volume plays a key part in the current AND

120
00:08:55,420 --> 00:08:58,380
future direction of a market.

121
00:08:58,380 --> 00:09:02,710
VOLUME HIGH OR LOW
As we have seen volume is the second most

122
00:09:02,710 --> 00:09:06,600
valuable item of data after the price itself.

123
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:11,410
Large volume confirms market activity and
that market participants are involved in the

124
00:09:11,410 --> 00:09:16,880
move, including smart money, who bring the
highest turnover to the market.

125
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:22,610
When the smart money are trading, it means
they are interested in price at certain levels

126
00:09:22,610 --> 00:09:25,920
and they literally push the price up or down.

127
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:30,890
Low volume tells us that there are very few
participants in the market, and that neither

128
00:09:30,890 --> 00:09:35,540
buyers nor sellers have any significant interest
in the price.

129
00:09:35,540 --> 00:09:42,270
In this scenario no smart money will be involved,
and therefore any moves from individual traders

130
00:09:42,270 --> 00:09:45,800
will be weak.

131
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:50,140
VOLUME AND TREND
Volume helps us to determine the health of

132
00:09:50,140 --> 00:09:51,140
a trend.

133
00:09:51,140 --> 00:09:57,460
An uptrend is strong and healthy if volume
increases as price moves with the trend and

134
00:09:57,460 --> 00:10:03,700
decreases when price goes counter trend (correction
periods or ‘pull backs’).

135
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:09,370
When prices are rising and volume is decreasing,
it tells traders that a trend is unlikely

136
00:10:09,370 --> 00:10:11,029
to continue.

137
00:10:11,029 --> 00:10:16,540
Price may still attempt to rise at a slower
pace, and once sellers take control (which

138
00:10:16,540 --> 00:10:23,000
is usually signified by an increase in volume
on a down bar or candle), prices will fall.

139
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:30,210
A downtrend is strong and healthy if volume
increases as prices move lower and decreases

140
00:10:30,210 --> 00:10:34,680
when the price begins to re-trace (pull back)
upwards.

141
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:40,570
When price is falling and volume is decreasing,
the downtrend is unlikely to continue.

142
00:10:40,570 --> 00:10:48,800
The price will either continue to decrease,
but at a slower pace or start to rise.

143
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:53,709
VOLUME AND REVERSALS
When volume spikes at certain price levels,

144
00:10:53,709 --> 00:10:58,080
traders know that this was an area of high
interest at that price level.

145
00:10:58,080 --> 00:11:03,060
If there is a great deal of interest, it means
the level is a key one.

146
00:11:03,060 --> 00:11:08,310
This simple observation of volume allows traders
to identify important support and resistance

147
00:11:08,310 --> 00:11:13,490
levels which could play a significant role
in the future.

148
00:11:13,490 --> 00:11:20,100
Where volume spikes are extreme (in other
words larger than any historical spikes nearby),

149
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:23,649
this is generally known as a volume climax.

150
00:11:23,649 --> 00:11:28,550
When this occurs traders should look for clues
for the future direction of the move from

151
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:36,149
the price itself, and this is often followed
by particular candle or price bar pattern.

152
00:11:36,149 --> 00:11:41,420
Single volume spikes can bring price to a
halt temporarily and these are often seen

153
00:11:41,420 --> 00:11:46,390
during fundamental and economic announcements
on a daily basis.

154
00:11:46,390 --> 00:11:52,910
Reversals, however, happen not over a single
day, but over a series of days.

155
00:11:52,910 --> 00:11:58,060
If higher than average volume stays in the
market for several days a huge volume spike

156
00:11:58,060 --> 00:12:03,670
- volume climax - will crown a point of market
reversal.

157
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:10,940
VOLUME AND BREAKOUTS
Volume can help to validate all kinds of breakouts.

158
00:12:10,940 --> 00:12:17,120
When the market is consolidating on low volume,
a pick up in volume can signify that a breakout

159
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:18,230
is due.

160
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:24,500
A breakout occurring on rising volume is a
valid breakout, while a breakout that attracted

161
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:31,740
no interest from traders occurring on low
volume, is likely to be false.

